    <h4>Larry X. Schor - Corporate Development Officer</h4>
    <p>
      Larry Schor has more than 25 years of experience in the health care industry with a primary interest in strategy, information technology and decision analytics, investment banking and business development.</p>

      <p>Most recently, Mr. Schor was a Principal & Managing Director of the Ansley Capital Group, a middle-market health care investment bank and management consultancy specializing in information technology, care management, and business process outsourcing.</p>

      <p>Previously, Larry was the founder and CEO of Helus, LLC, one of the first internet service providers of hosted clinical collaboration and workflow solutions for community based physicians; Senior Vice President & CIO for CoreSource, Inc., at the time the second largest employee benefits and workers compensation benefit administrators in the country; and President & CEO of Corporate Health Strategies, the decision analytics subsidiary of MetLife | Group Health.</p>

      <p>Larry holds a Bachelor of Science in Comparative Anatomy and a Bachelor of Arts in American Literature from Allegheny College and a Master of Public Health, Biostatistics and Epidemiology from Boston University.
    </p>
